RidgeRun Software License Agreement


Version 3.1


1. Notice

Read  this agreement  carefully. In  consideration for  evaluation and
potential purchase,  RidgeRun, LLC ("RidgeRun") is  willing to license
to you (hereafter "you" or "Customer") one copy of "RidgeRun Software"
for  evaluation  meant exclusively  for  use  on a  specific  hardware
evaluation module (EVM) which this product was configured for (defined
in section  2) for the  term of  this end-user license  agreement (the
"Agreement") only on the condition that you accept all of the terms of
this Agreement.  The  RidgeRun Software will be delivered  to you with
third  party software  distributed  under certain  open source  public
licenses,  such  as  the  GNU general  public  license  ("Open  Source
Software"). The  RidgeRun Software  and the  Open Source  Software are
collectively referred  to herein  as the "Software".   You irrevocably
accept and  agree to be bound  by this end-user license  Agreement and
applicable  licenses  for  the  Open Source  Software  by  installing,
downloading  or otherwise  using the  RidgeRun Software.   If you  are
agreeing to  these terms  on behalf  of a  company, you  represent and
warrant  to  RidgeRun  that  you  have full  authority  to  bind  such
entity. If  you do  not agree  to the terms  of this  end-user license
Agreement  and/or applicable  licenses for  the Open  Source Software,
uninstall, delete or otherwise remove  the RidgeRun Software from your
premises and you will have no right to use the Software.


2. RidgeRun Software

All software,  not specifically noted  as being the property  of other
corporations  or  part  of   other  license  agreements  are  RidgeRun
Software.

2.1 All content in the Software Development Kit "SDK" including source
code,  object code,  executables,  build system,  and applicable  user
documentation, corrections, releases,  and refinements related thereto
is RidgeRun Proprietary Information. 

2.2 A  targeted EVM  board license  is meant  for a  specific hardware
board evaluation module (EVM) as produced by a hardware computer board
supplier. RidgeRun's software product  is licensed exclusively for the
designated EVM board which is indicated through our download center or
as provided  by the EVM  manufacture for evaluation of  their hardware
module.   No reproduction,  distribution or  customization rights  are
implied  by the  words  "FreeSDK".  Customers  may  program, test  and
experiment on  the target  hardware platform only,  with no  rights to
reproduce or distribute RidgeRun software.

